1.   High fidelity. 2.   An electronic system for reproducing high-fidelity sound from radio or recordings. 1.   (Electronics)  a.   short for  high fidelity b.  ( as modifier ):  hi-fi equipment .  2.   (Electronics) a set of high-quality sound-reproducing equipment    1.   high fidelity.     2.   a phonograph, radio, or other sound-reproducing apparatus possessing high fidelity.     3.   of, pertaining to, or characteristic of such apparatus; high-fidelity. 